ated power, is reaching its limits. It has been extended by innovations in device architecture, introduction of new materials, and inventive techniques of patterning features of nanometer size. This decreasing size comes at an increasing cost, so most recent technology generations do not offer much advantage in terms of cost per transistor, or cost per function, when compared to previous nodes"--cProvided by publisher.  a44 0aNanoelectronicsxEquipment and supplies. 0aMicroelectronicsxEquipment and supplies. 0aElectronic apparatus and appliancesxMaterials.1 aBrozek, Tomasz,eeditor.1 aIniewski, Krzysztof,d1960-eeditor. 0aDevices, circuits, and systems.403University of Alberta Accessuhttp://marc.crcnetbase.com/isbn/9781482214918z(Unlimited Concurrent Users)  hUAINzCRC  aInternet AccesswLCc1i6748959-1001lINTERNETmUAINTERNETrYsYtE-RESOURCEu12/2/2014xE-BOOKzCRC01ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n2007019278bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/51135089